emove butterfly whisk<\/strong>, transfer whisked whites to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl and make sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Sauce"},{"content":"Place leeks and oil in mixing bowl then chop <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add wine, stock and water then, without measuring cup, cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>. Meanwhile, fold whisked egg whites into reserved soufflé base using a metal spoon."},{"content":"Heat oil in an oven-proof frying pan (Ø 26 cm) until sizzling, then add fresh salmon. Pour soufflé mix over salmon and bake for 15-17 minutes (200°C) until the top is lightly browned. Meanwhile, finish sauce."},{"content":"Add butter and lemon juice to mixing bowl then cook <b>1 min\/100°C\/speed 3<b> then blend <b>20 sec\/speed 3<b>. Add salt and pepper to taste and extra dill then transfer to a serving jug."},{"content":"Serve soufflé immediately with sauce and buttered toast on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["After placing souffle in the oven, fill a sauce boat or jug with hot water. Discard water just before pouring in the finished sauce; this will help keep the sauce warm.","The sauce can be made in advance, blended <strong>3 sec\/speed 5<\/strong>, then reheated <strong>3 min\/80°C\/speed <\/strong> just before serving.","This dish can be made for 2 people using the same quantity of souffle but only 2 pieces of salmon.","The sauce may be served with any simple fish dish."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h","4 portions"]}